  "texts": [
    "• While we encourage the release of code and data, we understand that this might not be possible, so \"No\" is an acceptable answer.",
    "Papers cannot be rejected simply for not including code, unless this is central to the contribution (e.g., for a new open-source benchmark).",
    "• The instructions should contain the exact command and environment needed to run to reproduce the results.",
    "See the NeurIPS code and data submission guidelines (https: //nips.cc/public/guides/CodeSubmissionPolicy) for more details.",
    "• The authors should provide instructions on data access and preparation, including how to access the raw data, preprocessed data, intermediate data, and generated data, etc."
  ],
